[&lt;kbd&gt;Live Example&lt;/kbd&gt;](http://ideone.com/MgDFOT)

This example assumes unique inputs, in which case a combination and permutation are the same. If you don&#39;t have unique inputs you&#39;re really asking for a _combination_ of these numbers. `next_combination` has been purposed here: http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2008/n2639.pdf You can copy that implementation if you find that you won&#39;t have unique inputs and just use that. You can also find out more about `next_combination` here: https://stackoverflow.com/a/35215540/2642059

